evaluation.response:
I care about what you're going through and I really see your frustrations. It's not about being an adult or handling things better. You don't deserve to be belittled by people who are supposed to care for you.

Taking time alone and having space is okay.&#x20;

Writing notes to yourself can be a way to copewith overwhelming feelings. Sometimes putting things into words can help clarify your thoughts and emotions, and find ways to cope with them.

Your feelings are valid and it's okay to not be okay. You have wonderful people who want to be there for you. Reach out to them when you need to talk to someone.

Home life can define a lot of this so it is common. &#x20;

You will make bigger progress the more that you can work at coping with this. That has gotten people through hell.
